column.name: isdefault
column.remarks: Indicates whether the Aggregate Chronology is a default or not. Datasets may have more than one default Aggregate Chronology, but may have only one default Aggregate Chronology per Age Type.

column.name: chronologyname
column.remarks: Optional name for the Chronology

column.name: ageboundyounger
column.remarks: The younger reliable age bound for the Aggregate Chronology

column.name: ageboundolder
column.remarks: The older reliable age bound for the Aggregate Chronology

column.name: notes
column.remarks: Free form notes or comments about the Aggregate Chronology

column.name: aggregatedatasetname
column.remarks: Name of Aggregate Dataset

column.name: aggregateordertypeid
column.remarks: FK: Links to AggregateOrderTypes table

column.name: notes
column.remarks: Free form notes about the Aggregate Order Type

column.name: collectionunitid
column.remarks: An arbitrary Collection Unit identification number.

column.name: handle
column.remarks: Code name for the Collection Unit. This code may be up to 10 characters, but an effort is made to keep these to 8 characters or less. Data are frequently distributed by Collection Unit, and the Handle is used for file names.

column.name: siteid
column.remarks: Site where CollectionUnit was located. Field links to Sites table.

column.name: colltypeid
column.remarks: Type of Collection Unit. Field links to the CollectionTypes table.

column.name: depenvtid
column.remarks: Depositional environment of the CollectionUnit. Normally, this key refers to the modern environment. For example, the site may be located on a colluvial slope, in which case the Depositional Environment may be Colluvium or Colluvial Fan. However, an excavation may extend into alluvial sediments, which represent a different depositional environment. These are accounted for by the Facies of the AnalysisUnit. Field links to the DepEnvtTypes table.

column.name: collunitname
column.remarks: Name of the Collection Unit. Examples: Core BPT82A, Structure 9, P4A Test 57. If faunal data are reported from a site or locality without explicit Collection Units, then data are assigned to a single Collection Unit with the name «Locality».

column.name: colldate
column.remarks: Date Collection Unit was collected.

column.name: colldevice
column.remarks: Device used for obtain Collection Unit. This field applies primarily to cores, for example «Wright square-rod piston corer (5 cm)».

column.name: gpslatitude
column.remarks: Precise latitude of the Collection Unit, typically taken with a GPS, although may be precisely measured from a map.

column.name: gpslongitude
column.remarks: Precise longitude of the Collection Unit, typically taken with a GPS, although may be precisely measured from a map.

column.name: gpsaltitude
column.remarks: Precise altitude of the Collection Unit, typically taken with a GPS or precisely obtained from a map.

column.name: gpserror
column.remarks: Error in the horizontal GPS coordinates, if known.

column.name: waterdepth
column.remarks: Depth of water at the Collection Unit location. This field applies mainly to Collection Units from lakes.

column.name: substrateid
column.remarks: Substrate or rock type on which the Collection Unit lies. Field links to the RockTypes table. This field is especially used for rodent middens.

column.name: slopeaspect
column.remarks: For Collection Units on slopes, the horizontal direction to which a slope faces measured in degrees clockwise from north. This field is especially used for rodent middens.

column.name: slopeangle
column.remarks: For Collection Units on slopes, the angle of slope from horizontal. field is especially used for rodent middens.

column.name: location
column.remarks: description of the location of the Collection Unit within the site.

column.name: notes
column.remarks: Free form notes or comments about the Collection Unit.

column.name: datasetid
column.remarks: Dataset identification number. Field links to Dataset table.

column.name: publicationid
column.remarks: Publication identification number. Field links to Publications table.

column.name: primarypub
column.remarks: Is «True» if the publication is the primary publication for the dataset.

table.name: dsageranges
table.viewSql: SELECT ageranges.datasetid, min(ageranges.younger) AS younger, max(ageranges.older) AS older, ageranges.agetypeid FROM ( SELECT ds.datasetid, CASE WHEN (ages.ageyounger IS NULL) THEN ages.age ELSE ages.ageyounger END AS younger, CASE WHEN (ages.ageolder IS NULL) THEN ages.age ELSE ages.ageolder END AS older, chrons.agetypeid FROM (((ndb.samples samples LEFT JOIN ndb.datasets ds ON ((samples.datasetid = ds.datasetid))) LEFT JOIN ndb.sampleages ages ON ((ages.sampleid = samples.sampleid))) LEFT JOIN ndb.chronologies chrons ON ((ages.chronologyid = chrons.chronologyid))) WHERE (chrons.isdefault = (1)::boolean)) ageranges GROUP BY ageranges.datasetid, ageranges.agetypeid;

table.name: dsdatasample
table.viewSql: SELECT ds.datasetid, sm.sampleid, dt.dataid, vr.variableid FROM (((ndb.datasets ds JOIN ndb.samples sm ON ((ds.datasetid = sm.datasetid))) JOIN ndb.data dt ON ((sm.sampleid = dt.sampleid))) JOIN ndb.variables vr ON ((dt.variableid = vr.variableid)));

table.name: dslinks
table.remarks: A view intended to link dataset ID, site ID and collection unit ID simply.
table.viewSql: SELECT ds.datasetid, ds.collectionunitid, sts.siteid FROM ((ndb.datasets ds LEFT JOIN ndb.collectionunits cu ON ((ds.collectionunitid = cu.collectionunitid))) LEFT JOIN ndb.sites sts ON ((cu.siteid = sts.siteid)));
